# ProjectFlo — Git & PR Conventions

## Branch names
- Format: `<type>/<short-description>`
- Types: `feature/`, `fix/`, `refactor/`, `chore/`
- Lowercase kebab-case; keep description under ~5 words.

## Commit messages
- Format: `<type>: <description>`
- Types: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `chore`, `docs`, `test`, `style`
- Imperative mood, no trailing period, first line <72 chars; add body for complex changes.

## Pull requests
- Title matches commit format: `<type>: <description>`
- Body should include: What changed, Why, Testing, and a checklist (build/test/lint/README/migrations as applicable).
- Keep PRs focused (one logical change).
- If touching pricing logic, update `PRICING_TOTALS_REFERENCE.md`.

